```

`lockMutex` gains a `self` parameter (see Step 2 below). On success, reset `self.consecutive_mutex_timeouts = 0`. On timeout, increment and log at threshold. Callers of `acquire()` propagate `MutexTimeout` to the handshake path — new connections fail rather than silently accumulate leaked state. The `.err` log line at threshold 3 is the alerting signal for operators to investigate (stuck holder or contention spike requiring restart).

